This paper is about speech recognition, which is a natural language processing task, and therefore likely falls under the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of a language model as a strong prior, which suggests that it may also be relevant to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a semi-supervised learning approach, which could be relevant to "Systems and Control" (cs.SY) and "Sound" (cs.SD) sub-categories.
